</CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#D5D4D5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ufelishannasecretlight.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Felishanna Secretlight</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I live here.... get out.</span><br> <font color=#000033>(2/16/02 8:00:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/feqasylumcleric.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=322.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire</span><hr size=1> OOC.<br>
<br>
1. The spawn in Sol B and the spawn in Skyfire are independent. Doing one does not cause the other to spawn. They have nothing to do with eachother. AT ALL. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2. The Skyfire Ragefire is a STATIC (not a wandering) spawn, but his timing is random. He has a long repop period (currently looking like 0-2 days after a patch, and 4-6 days thereafter, far far too long <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). Being static, however, you can if you have the huge time needed, decide to camp him.<br>
<br>
3. You can camp him day and night. Or you can pop in from time to time to look. That's up to you. You will be very lucky now that everyone knows how this new spawn works to find him up by just looking, with no other cleric there already (but it could just happen).<br>
<br>
4. You cannot schedule this on the calendar. Don't even think about it. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
5. If you are camping him alone, for days and nights (somehow), and he pops for you, most others would respect your camp IF you have a raid force strong enough to kill him on the way to help you very quickly. You don't *have* to have anyone else there with you, as long as they can get there fast. VERY fast. If you do camp him, it is better if you camp him with your cleric, not some alt monk or such, as someone who is sitting next to you camping him with their actual cleric chracter will not be impressed by that. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  You could log the cleric at the camp and sit there on a safer alt though.<br>
<br>
6. If you are camping him with other clerics there (this is likely), you can negotiate with the other clerics there, and that's between you to decide how you will handle it if he pops, and it will depend on your attitude and the attitudes of those who are there also. All clerics have to go through this trial of pain, so be nice to eachother. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Yesterday I (well, Mage Suzanna) came to help one cleric kill Ragefire, to find two clerics were there and that they had agreed to roll on who got the drop, which they did. It was handled very civally and honourably (and no doubt heartbreaking for the one who didn't win the roll).<br>
<br>
But you better be fast, and have 4 or 5 or more very strong groups ready to come help you at a moment's notice. Not easy to do for non-raiding-guild folks. Don't expect another raiding force to wait if you cannot get folks there if its a bad time for you, nothing you can do in that case except help your fellow cleric or leave.<br>
<br>
7. On Lanys, some people will not respect the camp at all, and will not negotiate at all, and will consider the spawn fully FFA, and will not care how long you have been there or even if you have a raid 60 seconds away or even in zone already but not quite ready. No matter how rude this is, there is nothing you could do but either accept it quietly, or socially slam such behaviour with all your friends afterwards, to isolate this kind of attitude, but it will not change the result, so be warned of this. Verant will not get involved unless your raid engaged Ragefire first and then another raid attacked him.<br>
<br>
8. There are a lot of views of clerics on this spawn on ALL servers on www.eqcleric.com, go to the message boards, and then to the Quests Forum. You will find a wealth of advice, comments and opinions there.<br>
<br>
