<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Why I hate the Roll</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
First, in order to understand why I have such a strong view on this particular topic, you need to understand the kind of player I am. I'm an RPGer from way back, and one game, I gm-ed the same world for 5 years with the same core of players who played 3 different generations of their first characters family. I have a great love of the epic storyline (thx robert jordan), and I came to Everquest *thrilled* at the prospect of an RPG where the people around you knew nothing of you but what the model looked like and what you presented to them....let's face it. Playing a table top, it may be &quot;Ludwig the Big Bold and Beautiful&quot; but you're still looking at Vinny and his pot belly and bad haircut.<br>
<br>
You see, I'm not anyone special in real life. I'm a 30 year old guy that writes plays and short stories in his spare time and does UNIX administration for a living (because being a playwright, even a popular one, is the same as starving to death :P). I, and many others, drawn to the fantasy genre come here because of the concept of being &quot;the average joe that rises to the level of hero&quot; that we have read time and time again in our pulp fantasy novels. <br>
<br>
I dove into EQ head first, creating a barbarian shaman on Mithaniel Marr, and she was one bawdy wench who kept her barbarian warriors in line. It never really dawned on me that while I was roleplaying, THEY weren't, which created all sorts of bizarre situations once it occurred to me that they thought I really WAS her. But that's beyond the point. The point is, I threw myself into the character, and the quests....I loved the totemic armour quests.... In fact, I love the quests in this game more than just about any other aspect.<br>
<br>
When I came to Lanys, I made Rugen and I decided I'd be much less Roleplay than I had done with Kal, just so as to avoid such horribly strange situations as I was in there. But that never changed my internal monologues. The Plane of Growth raids? It may have been a fun raid, lewt, and whatever to other people, but it was always a vendetta for Rugen to take to Tunare the slaughter of his people right to the goddess that smiled upon her druid's actions. <br>
<br>
All my &quot;life&quot; as Rugen, I've stuck to that model that draws me to the epic story. Average Joe that becomes a *hero*. I went to do my entire gold suit from Ro at 20 so that I could be dressed in gold for my wedding to Cubbie. &quot;Oh, you're crazy! Some of those mobs are in really dangerous places...they are too hard, you'll never do it. Just level, you'll be able to do them with ease later. blah blah blah&quot;<br>
<br>
I didn't care. Heros never listen when they are told something can't be done, because they know better. Or are just too stupid NOT to know better. Either way. I did it. Because it was there, and I COULD.<br>
<br>
And I was so damn proud. Stupid, I know, it's a video game. But the character's story and overcoming odds people didn't think I could, made it all the more worth it.<br>
<br>
So what does this have to do with hating the roll?<br>
<br>
&quot;You'll never get your epic without an uber guild. You'll never get your epic at 50, just level to 60 and then get it. You'll never get your epic because Rage is a contested spawn.&quot;<br>
<br>
But Rugen was too stupid to listen to people, and he did it anyway.<br>
<br>
And be damned if I didn't feel &quot;a hero&quot;.<br>
<br>
I hate the roll because it tells people that they aren't good enough to be the hero of their own story. I hate the roll because it makes people buy into the bullshit that only an uberguild can be the hero in a FFA world. I hate the roll because it (in my eyes) is an admission of &quot;I can't do this except the easy way&quot;.<br>
<br>
I've always been too stupid to believe any of that, and any cleric that sends me a tell about the epic quest (and there are a lot) usually starts out with &quot;I know I can't do this til I quit my guild and go join an uber guild, but.....&quot;<br>
<br>
And I stress to them, as hard as I can, that none of that is true. You can do your epic in a small guild, you CAN do your epic before you are 60, and you sure as hell CAN beat an uberguild to a mob. If you want it bad enough. <br>
<br>
Heros don't ask the rewards or the bad guys to line up and wait for them....ala:<br>
<br>
