So yeah. I do support the FFA on Rage. But it's not because I'm a greedy grubby bastard like Felis would like to believe. It's because I loathe what I see as the inherent message in the roll. <br>
<br>
Why don't we have any stories of King Wilbur of Camelot because he and Arthur rolled over who got the sword? Because that's not the story of a hero.<br>
<br>
So yeah. I despise the roll, and I'm pretty darn vocal about it. Do I fault someone for taking the roll and getting their epic? No. It's a great item. I just wish it were more about the epic struggle and story of a hero winning despite all the odds, and not so much &quot;the odds are too hard. let's roll.&quot;<br>
